•
Highlight Superiority: Articulate specific areas where the proposed standard demonstrably surpasses the capabilities of these industry leaders, providing quantifiable evidence (e.g., advanced statistical rigor, customizability, security features).

•
Integrated Tooling Strategy: Detail a strategy for developing integrated tooling for experiment design, execution, and analysis, comparable to mature platforms, reducing the need for significant custom integration effort.

•
Operational Simplicity for Advanced Methods: Provide a plan for making advanced statistical methods (mSPRT, CUPED) accessible and operationally simple for teams without deep statistical expertise, potentially through automated guidance and simplified interfaces.



5.2. Proactive Strategy for Emerging Experimentation Techniques

•
Mandate: Outline a proactive strategy for integrating and leveraging emerging experimentation techniques (e.g., causal inference methods, synthetic control groups, advanced sequential testing beyond mSPRT) to maintain a competitive edge. This includes:

•
Research & Development Roadmap: Establish a research and development roadmap for continuously evaluating and piloting new experimentation methodologies.

•
Integration Roadmap: Provide a roadmap for integrating promising emerging techniques into the Level 10 Enterprise A/B Testing Platform.



